{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"WOnXV41UlGcOQzEoTZzJU","title":"Glossary","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[],"anchors":{"glossary":{"type":"header","text":"Glossary","value":"glossary","line":8,"column":0}},"fname":"Glossary","updated":1636692955326,"created":1635209708973,"parent":"PhD","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"921ebdab63d4027196b66072e7cb2c5d","custom":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"glossary\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#glossary\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Glossary</h1>\n<p>Glossary of Mathematical symbols and terms to help keep track of notation - trying to be as consistent as possible, but this is not always feasible.</p>\n<p>As usual, anything with a hat over it denotes an estimator version, and no hat is assumed to be the true population.</p>\n<p>Note that these notes will try to use notation that is consistent as possible, but this is difficult given that everyone in the literature uses their own notation. Any differences will be noted.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<table><thead><tr><th>Symbol</th><th>Definition</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>N</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span></span></span></span></span></td><td>number of macroeconomic time series</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span></td><td>length of macroeconomic time series</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">r</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span></span></span></span></span></td><td>true number of factors</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">q</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">q</span></span></span></span></span></td><td>true number of primitive shocks (dynamic factors)</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f_t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2805559999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.10764em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></td><td>true factors</td><td>Typically used interchangeably to mean the true space spanned by the true factors</td></tr><tr><td><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>λ</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\lambda_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.84444em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">λ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></td><td>true loadings</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>g</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">g_t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2805559999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.03588em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></td><td>so called pseudo factors</td><td>static factors estimated without accounting for possible breaks</td></tr><tr><td><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">k</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span></span></td><td>break point/break date</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>τ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\tau</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1132em;\">τ</span></span></span></span></span></td><td>break fraction</td><td>note that <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>τ</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\tau T = k</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1132em;\">τ</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span></span>; Note that a consistent estimator for <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>k</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">k</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span></span> is much harder to get, as <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>τ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\tau</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1132em;\">τ</span></span></span></span></span> will typically achieve convergence much more easily as <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T \\rightarrow \\infty</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∞</span></span></span></span></span>. The practical difference between the two is mostly a finite sample problem and left as an open question.</td></tr></tbody></table>","noteIndex":{"id":"PhD","title":"PhD Homepage","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"roadmap","alias":"roadmap","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":451},"end":{"line":12,"column":12,"offset":462},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"roadmap"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Meeting","alias":"Meeting","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":464},"end":{"line":14,"column":12,"offset":475},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"Meeting"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"TODO","alias":"TODO","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":477},"end":{"line":16,"column":9,"offset":485},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"TODO"}}],"anchors":{"quick-links":{"type":"header","text":"Quick Links","value":"quick-links","line":17,"column":0},"to-do-list":{"type":"header","text":"To do List","value":"to-do-list","line":25,"column":0}},"fname":"root","updated":1636683885086,"created":1595961348801,"parent":null,"children":["CQTUwoXQNcd0Y7la7IaAn","AiXOWFsdvi3BPZxcUMjIi","MsmFdXyWfizd5g8GGcObD","MXHvc8bQbNRRVCB0UogRy","T4FN6sDHfA9wxiZ7Dg5WX","jtZSk246bVVDfJy6cdpS1","2qGHFR7CcKOE0Meu7UU6D","qGmGYptDKW2WLwlsu2xJw","GvwoAWaYZxq1czYi3t3k4","ZIDZSAYP9a9L7jYhVMgcz","WOnXV41UlGcOQzEoTZzJU","fhf7Gdr3mhOUG1mU5twC6","AOvKFmg0tBcGmUASXaALX","qDVp6IFHf6FiUdSgxwZMA","HgXYpL8CJLCszNUOmbHhP","fHzGITjWkNNkiwsQpdex4","umGHrdI4OaLoU8OOAOdkL","aQw5xJBpqunSJYCfXXAls","0R61RLuT7e3hswR2v6o0w","AuDqSlWn0PlsSo8JdLgrR","ElqQePaEuSSz7pSeO1gNc","BMClpTRP3V8ITqM7R4kh0","1ruiVSk3lFpEOUNqPnYti","FNflnQbSXuMwTtni2C8is","y0rpX1u3Lz3vpUFro9TcW"],"data":{},"contentHash":"d7de26282e04813f39247a66c191dd07","custom":{"stub":false,"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"body":"\nWelcome to my website!\n\nThis website has been built using Dendron, and each topic has been collated into collapsible sections on the left hand side. Below is a high level overview showing how each section is connected for ease of navigation.\n\n\n\nDendron has incredibly powerful search functionality due to good indexing, even outside of working in raw .md files. Simply use the search bar at the top of the website to find something.\n\n## Quick Links\n\n[[roadmap]]\n\n[[Meeting]]\n\n[[TODO]]\n\n## To do List\n\nType up Bai and Ng assumptions\n\nInvestigate Bates et al Assumptions\n\nInvestigate consistency of using an estimated break point in conjunction with BNIC\nThis seems to be consistent using k_tilde that itself may be Op(1)\n\nFix up BP test for better interface (low priority)\n\nImplement simulated Andrews exp and mean Wald/LM tests\n\n- look into RSpectra package (supposedly faster eigen)\n- not sure whether to rename this to SFM or not (lots of legacy code that needs to be changed)\n\nData\nFix and clean data for \n- AUMD (on hold, need to find date index)\n- FREDQD\n- CANMD (should be straightforward)\n- CANQD\n- UKMD (should be straightforward)\n\nInvestigate further sources of time series that could be used during COVID\n\nImplement truly dynamic factor models (Forni) using Dynamic PCA\n- BIG task\n- read into dynamic PCA\n- read into testing no. of dynamic factors\n- do not believe there is a literature focusing on breaks in the dynamic setup\n- implement dynamic PCA\n- implement testing no of factors, (look into ICshocks functions and make this interface better)\n- implement testing no of factors using AW test\n\nImplement BKW standard test (non sequential)\n\nFix up BKW test\n- implement a general plot method which plots *something* on the y axis, but most importantly, date on the x axis with estimated break dates, and each partition labelled with the no. of factors as determined by some consistent estimator\n\nFix up BE test\n- so that there is a consistent interface for accessing this\n\n\n\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":3,"useFMTitle":false,"useNoteTitleForLink":true,"noLegacyNoteRef":true,"mermaid":true,"useKatex":true,"usePrettyRefs":true,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"site":{"copyAssets":true,"siteHierarchies":["root"],"siteRootDir":"docs","usePrettyRefs":true,"title":"Ze Yu","description":"Personal knowledge space","siteLastModified":true,"gh_edit_branch":"main","duplicateNoteBehavior":{"action":"useVault","payload":["vault"]},"siteUrl":"https://zeyuz35.github.io/","usePrettyLinks":true,"siteNotesDir":"notes","siteFaviconPath":"favicon.ico","gh_edit_link":true,"gh_e